PiperOrigin-RevId: 324898684

Add TFRecord formatted vocabularies support to TFT analyzers and mappers.

This change slightly affects text formatted vocabularies as well:
 * Numerical vocabularies are now also sorted in reverse lexicographical order
 * TFTransformOutput.vocabulary_file_by_name will now return None if the requested vocabulary does not exist

In this change:
 * A `file_format` parameter is added to vocabulary related analyzers and mappers
 * The vocabulary write code path can now write it in TFRecord format
 * Vocabulary related methods of TFTransformOutput have been updated to handle TFRecord vocabularies correctly.
 * TFT now also allows table init ops of type InitializeTableFromDataset
 * The TFT graph analyzer is modified to allow non analyzer-related placeholders in FuncGraphs if those are inputs to tf.functions.
 * Change uses of `tf.feature_column.categorical_column_with_vocabulary_file` since that assumes always text file which is no longer the case for TFT.
